title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1982-04-06
description:
Set I
Cold Rain & Snow-> Promised Land, Candyman-> CC Rider, Brown Eyed Women, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Big Railroad Blues, Looks Like Rain, Jack A Roe, It's All Over Now, Might As Well
Set II
Shakedown Street-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> The Other One-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text:
crazy As Shakedown is coming to a close their is a very quick Crazy Fingersish tease. I think they had sound checked it earlier in the day. Maybe not the Shakedown as sound check but Crazy fingers. We all know in 1985 the boys gave us 2 Shakedown Crazy Fingers ( Red Rocks, Kaiser ) point being I wouldn't put it past them considering above. 
 As far as the sound here I SON'T know it could get much better then previous versions but it did. You nailed it on this Matrix . 
JUST AMAZING
 Am almost completely threw listening to this show for at least 20th time and I am blown away again. The boys were so very on in spring 1982. Fun time to be beginning my tour life.
GETS MORE THEN 5 STARS. Trust me and the other reviews ....
